text:
Finnair celebrates the delivery of first A350 XWB Published on : Thursday, October 8, 2015
Airbus and Finnair marked a key milestone on 7 October 2015, with the delivery of the first A350 XWB jetliner for this Helsinki-based carrier.
Finnair – which was the first airline to select the A350 XWB – became the initial European carrier to receive this highly-efficient member of Airbus’ market-leading product line.
This landmark handover marks another step in the long relationship between Airbus and Finnair – which is an all-Airbus operator for the aircraft over 100 seats in its fleet. Finnair plans to begin scheduled long-haul service with the A350 XWB in late November – initially between Helsinki and Shanghai, before commencing service on routes to other Asian cities.
Take flight with Airbus and Finnair – relive exclusive online coverage from the historic delivery ceremony in Toulouse, France, including videos, photos and news articles, and more.
Source: Airbus.
